reviewText:
A very disappointing film, not saved by some (not all) good songs.
Full of clichs, poorly solved side-plots, shallow.
It fails to be a comedy and fails at being a musical.
Beautiful landscapes though and some good dancing.

If you like Juan Gabriel, I think you'll enjoy this movie.  Might be a bit B quality but still lovable and worth watching, I actually watched it the second night and enjoyed it more for catching things I didn't see the first time.
Whas not what i was expecting.
Excellent Mexican musical with songs by Juan Gabriel. Funny and different. A real Juan Gabriel experience.
Hoping it is enjoyed a lot.
